<br>
&quot;I set out to do this quest yesterday and completed it today on the Firiona Vie server, where the Trivial Loot Code forces you to do it in the appropriate level range or not at all. <br>
<br>
At first, I was afraid, I was petrified (oh, wait, wrong song)... <br>
<br>
 Lesser Faydark scares the bejeepers out of me, as it should any sane person. Between the Brownies and Equestrielle the Corrupted, it's just a suicidal zone for any quest. <br>
<br>
However, it is possible to do this one at 13-16 (I did it at 15th), without Wolf Form. It just take some creativity, some caution, a lot of patience, and a ranger. <br>
<br>
The first two Putrescent Hearts I got just travelling down the path from the Greater Faydark zoneline to the first fork. I found a Rancorous Ghast somewhere along there, pulled it back to the Greater Faydark zoneline, and killed it. The Brownies don't seem to bother you there, although Equestrielle the Corrupted does, so keep your eyes peeled. <br>
<br>
In my experience, the Rancorous Ghasts with Putrescent Hearts seemed to pop up somewhere along that path sometime during the day. I had absolutely no luck with them at night--they didn't even show up there, although I can't say definitively that they don't show up there at night. They do, however, show up during the day. I can say that definitively. <br>
<br>
So, if you stick close to the zone entrance and wait, the Rancorous Ghasts will show up eventually. Kill them, pull back to the Greater Faydark zoneline, recover, and head back to that first fork. <br>
<br>
I hired three Rangers to help me track, and this proved very effective at getting the last two Putrescent Hearts I needed. The Rangers have to be cautious, however. Running all over the zone gets a person killed quick, even with Camoflage, and then you spend the next hour (realtime) recovering bodies. A Ranger with a healthy fear of Brownies and Equestrielle the Corrupted is a useful Ranger in this situation. I Camoflaged him or her (as the case may be), cast Spirit of Wolf on him or her, let him or her track the Rancorous Ghasts and pull them back to the Greater Faydark zoneline to kill them. <br>
<br>
Two of the Rangers I hired got killed. Both of them had a tendency to want to wander all over the zone; one was killed by a Brownie and Equestrielle, the other by Brownies. The Tenth Autumn Ranger I hired, the one responsible for helping me find the last two Putrescent Hearts, did not get killed, mainly  because the zone scared the daylights out of him (as it should any sane person). <br>
<br>
 I wound up finishing this quest in little under 24 hours, realtime, without using Wolf Form. I was killed once by a Brownie on the first attempt in the zone, and once again by Equestrielle the Corrupted right at the Greater Faydark zoneline (I almost made it through, too!), and that was it. I didn't even lose a level, as I had expected to (and as Xelissen had told me he had). If you're very cautious, very patient, and stick close to the Greater Faydark zoneline, you'll be able to complete it. <br>
<br>
 Lasgalen, Fifteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare, Tailor/Blacksmith/Potter, Kelethin, Firiona Vie Server&quot;<br>
